107
00:06:08,602 --> 00:06:09,602
Finally!

108
00:06:11,602 --> 00:06:13,602
I couldn't have waited any longer!

109
00:06:17,602 --> 00:06:18,602
Good morning, children!

110
00:06:18,602 --> 00:06:19,602
Good morning!

111
00:06:19,602 --> 00:06:21,602
Where have you been so long? We've been waiting so long!

112
00:06:21,602 --> 00:06:23,602
So? How rude of me!

113
00:06:23,602 --> 00:06:25,602
Please help me down.

114
00:06:25,602 --> 00:06:26,602
Yes.

115
00:06:27,602 --> 00:06:28,602
Thank you very much.

116
00:06:28,602 --> 00:06:30,602
Would you please carry my bag into the hut?

117
00:06:30,602 --> 00:06:32,602
Yes, I'd love to.

118
00:06:32,602 --> 00:06:34,602
There they are!

119
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:35,602
I think so, too.

120
00:06:36,602 --> 00:06:37,562
Oh!

121
00:06:37,562 --> 00:06:41,762
Oh, why can't you just invent more comfortable horses?

122
00:06:41,762 --> 00:06:42,962
Everything hurts me.

123
00:06:42,962 --> 00:06:44,362
I can imagine.

124
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,562
Grandfather?

125
00:06:46,562 --> 00:06:47,862
Good morning.

126
00:06:47,862 --> 00:06:53,762
Would you say it would be shameless if I asked you again for such a wonderful
glass of fresh goat's milk?

127
00:06:53,762 --> 00:06:56,162
Not at all.

128
00:06:56,162 --> 00:06:57,262
I made it.

129
00:06:57,262 --> 00:06:59,362
Well, thank you.

130
00:06:59,362 --> 00:07:00,762
Now finally say it.

131
00:07:00,762 --> 00:07:01,962
What should I say?

132
00:07:01,962 --> 00:07:03,262
What's in the bag.

133
00:07:03,262 --> 00:07:03,962
Come with me.

134
00:07:03,962 --> 00:07:05,856
We'll just take a look.

135
00:07:05,856 --> 00:07:07,856
Good-bye.

136
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:16,650
Oh, there's nothing better.

137
00:07:16,650 --> 00:07:18,650
Now show it to us, please.

138
00:07:18,650 --> 00:07:19,650
What did you buy?

139
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:21,650
Oh, that's what you mean.

140
00:07:23,650 --> 00:07:27,650
A wonderful bedclothes for everyone and a head pillow here.

141
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:31,650
A warm night's dress for Clara, but also wear it.

142
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:35,650
You know, my child, the nights are getting colder again.

143
00:07:35,650 --> 00:07:38,650
And then a few work trousers for the palm oil.

144
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:40,650
So, is that what you want to know?

145
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,650
Is that all?

146
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:43,650
Yes.

147
00:07:43,856 --> 00:07:47,856
We thought you would buy us a present. You also brought something for Peter.

148
00:07:47,856 --> 00:07:49,856
Yes, we thought so.

149
00:07:49,856 --> 00:07:52,856
Well, then I have to buy you something.

150
00:07:52,856 --> 00:07:54,856
Yes, it doesn't have to be anything big and expensive.

151
00:07:54,856 --> 00:07:56,856
Chocolate!

152
00:07:56,856 --> 00:07:59,856
Well, nice. But that's why I'm not going down the mountain right away.

153
00:07:59,856 --> 00:08:01,456
Oh, too bad.

154
00:08:01,456 --> 00:08:05,576
No, certainly not. You can't ask for that. You'll have to wait.

155
00:08:05,576 --> 00:08:07,896
Besides, I'm terribly tired again.

156
00:08:07,896 --> 00:08:09,336
I just don't believe it.

157
00:08:09,336 --> 00:08:13,296
But listen, Clara. You have the whole closet full of toys at home.

158
00:08:13,296 --> 00:08:16,336
What more do you need? Now go and play outside.

159
00:08:17,136 --> 00:08:20,176
I'm sorry, Grandmother, but I still don't believe it.

160
00:08:20,176 --> 00:08:23,736
Well, you torturers, I have a present for you.

161
00:08:23,736 --> 00:08:24,432
Grandma!

162
00:08:24,432 --> 00:08:26,432
Show me what you've hidden!

163
00:08:26,432 --> 00:08:28,432
You can't see my present.

164
00:08:28,432 --> 00:08:30,432
Can you give something like that away?

165
00:08:30,432 --> 00:08:32,432
And if you can give something like that away.

166
00:08:32,432 --> 00:08:36,432
How are we supposed to recognize it if you give us something transparent?

167
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:40,432
I don't give you anything transparent, I give you something invisible.

168
00:08:41,432 --> 00:08:45,432
So, and now I don't want to hear anything from you anymore. Wait until tomorrow.

169
00:08:45,432 --> 00:08:47,432
Yes, but just say it.

170
00:08:47,432 --> 00:08:49,344
No, I can't do that.

171
00:08:49,344 --> 00:08:51,844
Let us guess, with hot and cold.

172
00:08:51,844 --> 00:08:55,344
That looks like you. If you don't want to give up, you don't want to give up.

173
00:08:55,344 --> 00:08:57,844
And now you're trying to get me around with all means.

174
00:08:57,844 --> 00:08:58,844
Why not?

175
00:08:58,844 --> 00:09:01,344
Keep going, Heidi. Maybe you can do it.

176
00:09:01,344 --> 00:09:04,344
She already looks like she's about to tell us.

177
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:05,844
I don't think so.

178
00:09:05,844 --> 00:09:07,844
Will you at least go for a walk with us?

179
00:09:07,844 --> 00:09:10,844
No, I'm tired. I want to rest today.

180
00:09:10,844 --> 00:09:12,844
I'm not used to the mountain air yet.

181
00:09:12,844 --> 00:09:14,344
Why don't you go to Peter?

182
00:09:14,344 --> 00:09:16,844
Me? If Clara has nothing against it?

183
00:09:17,184 --> 00:09:19,184
I'd like to go back to the pasture.

184
00:09:19,184 --> 00:09:23,184
Besides, I have to make sure that the little ghost gets good herbs.

185
00:09:23,184 --> 00:09:25,184
Don't come back so late.

186
00:09:25,184 --> 00:09:26,184
Say hello to Peter.

187
00:09:26,184 --> 00:09:29,184
Why? I don't understand. Don't the goats eat on their own?

188
00:09:29,184 --> 00:09:33,184
Yes, but she always gives him special herbs so that they give good milk.

189
00:09:33,184 --> 00:09:35,184
Especially for me.

190
00:09:35,184 --> 00:09:39,184
I've always said it. Heidi is really nice.

191
