It doesn't smell at all. I didn't think it was right that she complained.

197
00:10:17,138 --> 00:10:20,138
I mean Mrs. Rottenmeier, she always complained.

198
00:10:20,138 --> 00:10:25,138
I can imagine. She must have always walked around with her cloth in front of her
nose.

199
00:10:30,282 --> 00:10:33,282
What do you think of Clara's grandmother?

200
00:10:33,282 --> 00:10:35,282
Very decent.

201
00:10:35,282 --> 00:10:39,282
I also imagined her to be worse.

202
00:10:41,282 --> 00:10:43,282
She's not bad at all.

203
00:10:43,282 --> 00:10:45,282
Because of me.

204
00:10:52,522 --> 00:10:57,522
Mrs. Rottenmeier said that I never had a nap, but that's not true.

205
00:10:57,522 --> 00:11:00,522
We always lay on the meadow and dreamed.

206
00:11:00,522 --> 00:11:04,522
We then looked at the clouds and everyone had to say what they were reminded of.

207
00:11:04,522 --> 00:11:06,522
Most of them look like sheep.

208
00:11:06,522 --> 00:11:07,522
And that was fun.

209
00:11:07,522 --> 00:11:08,522
Yes, and how.

210
00:11:08,522 --> 00:11:12,522
You know, sometimes I wish so much that I can walk.

211
00:11:12,522 --> 00:11:16,522
I know, but you have to be healthy and strong first.

212
00:11:16,522 --> 00:11:18,522
Maybe you can do it one day.

213
00:11:18,522 --> 00:11:21,522
Tell me, have you ever tried to stand up?

214
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:24,208
But no!

215
00:11:24,208 --> 00:11:26,208
What do you mean, but no?

216
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:31,208
Me, at your place, I would try it every day, secretly, so long until I suddenly
can.

217
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:35,208
Well, I've tried it before, but it didn't work.

